{"lemma":"عَصَبِ","slug":"عَصَبِ","root":"ع.ص.ب","root_slug":"ع-ص-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ص-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":22},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29265","n29266","n29271","n29272","n29273","n29274"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to twist, wrap around"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fold tightly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bound or bind, to tie"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to castrate via a band around testicles"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bandage"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to draw people together, to assemble"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to surround, to encompass"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to surround, to encompass; to include, to hold or reckon together, such as the entirety of one's relations, to be of the same identity"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to obligate, to bind responsibility or consequences to; especially with phrases like بِ (bi) + رَأْس (raʔs, “head”)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause a thing to be twisted, or wrapped around"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to swaddle, to cause a thing to be tightly folded around"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bandage, to tourniquet"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turban, to wrap one's brow with a band"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turban, to wrap one's brow with a band; to crown, to declare or cause one to be a chief"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nerve"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sinew, tendon"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"muscle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"band, ribbon, scarf"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chieftain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandees","tags":["in-plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"somewhat distant relations","tags":["in-plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bindweed (Convolvulus)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.sˤa.ba/","/ʕasˤ.sˤa.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29265","headword_ar":"عَصَبَ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He twisted"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a thing], or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"round:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA:) this is the primary signification: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he folded"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it]; (A, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he folded"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tightly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it], or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tied"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it]: (A, Mgh, K, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"denotes the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"binding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing with another thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lengthwise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or [more commonly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"around."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) See also 2, first sentence. [And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoSuwbN","text_ar":"مَعْصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He twisted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spun,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thread. (K, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put together"},{"kind":"text","text":"thread,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"it, previously to dyeing it. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkabo$a","text_ar":"الكَبْشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K, *] aor. as above, (K,) and so the inf. n., (S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tightly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the testicles of the ram, in order that they might fall, without his extracting them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K:) and in like manner one says of a goat, (K,) and of other beasts. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAqapa","text_ar":"النَّاقَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Msb, K, *) aor. as above, (K,) and so the inf. n., (Msb, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbN","text_ar":"عِصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtSbhA","text_ar":"اعتصبها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound the thighs of the she-camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lower parts of her nostrils,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a cord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,) in order that she might yield her milk copiously: (Msb, K, TA:) and (O)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxi*a Aln~aAqapi","text_ar":"فَخِذَ النَّاقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound the thigh of the she-camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"] for that purpose. (S, O.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSuwbN","text_ar":"عَصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Hence one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTaY EalaY AlEaSobi","text_ar":"اَعْطَى عَلَى العَصْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave by means of force."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivoliY laA yadir~u biAlEiSaAbi","text_ar":"مِثْلِى لَا يَدِرُّ بِالعِصَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one as I am will not give by means of force."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabato farojahaA","text_ar":"عَصَبَتْ فَرْجَهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bound her vulva with a bandage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Al$~ajarapa","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الشَّجَرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drew together the branches of the tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that were straggling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of a rope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then beat it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,) in order that its leaves might fall. (S, O, TA.) [Golius assigns this signification also to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaS~aba","text_ar":"عَصَّبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as on the authority of the S, in which I do not find it.] El-Hajjáj said, (S, TA,) when preaching to the people at El-Koofeh, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^aEoSiban~akumo","text_ar":"لَاَعْصِبَنَّكُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSoba Als~alami","text_ar":"عَصْبَ السَّلَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alamapi","text_ar":"السَّلَمَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly draw you together and beat you as one does the selem"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the selemeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salamap","text_ar":"سَلَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a tree of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":", having thorns, and its leaves are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraZ","text_ar":"قَرَظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with which hides are tanned: [but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraZN","text_ar":"قَرَظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the removal of the leaves with the hand being difficult on account of the many thorns, its branches are drawn together and bound tightly with a rope; then the beater pulls them towards him, and beats them with his staff; whereupon the leaves become scattered for the cattle and for him who desires to gather them. (TA.) Or this is done, (S, O, TA,) accord. to A 'Obeyd, (S, O,) only (TA) when they desire to cut down the selemeh, that they may get at the stock. (S, O, TA.) [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA tuEoSabu salamaAtuhu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا تُعْصَبُ سَلَمَاتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one will not have his selemehs bound round with a rope, and beaten"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a prov., applied to a strong, mighty man, not to be subdued nor abased. (A, * TA.) And one says also of winds,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoSibu Al$~ajara Einoda duruwjihaA fiyhi","text_ar":"تَعْصِبُ الشَّجَرَ عِنْدَ دُرُوجِهَا فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They compress the branches of the trees, as though they bound them round, in their passage among them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and such winds are termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAy^ibu","text_ar":"عَصَايِبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Alqawoma","text_ar":"عَصَبَ القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an affair, or event,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drew the people together, and became severe to them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba SadoEa AlzujaAjapi biDab~apK mino fiD~apK","text_ar":"عَصَبَ صَدْعَ الزُجَاجَةِ بِضَبَّةٍ مِنْ فِضَّةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a smith)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repaired the crack of the glass vessel by putting round it a band of silver."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba biraA^osi qawomihi AlEaAra","text_ar":"عَصَبَ بِرَاْسِ قَوْمِهِ العَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made disgrace to befall his people"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though he bound it upon the head of their chief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the head of each of them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) It is related in a trad. respecting the battle of Bedr, that 'Otbeh the son of Rabee'ah said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirojiEuwA walaA tuqaAtiluwA waA@EoSibuwhaA biraA^osiY","text_ar":"اِرْجِعُوا وَلَا تُقَاتِلُوا وَا@عْصِبُوهَا بِرَاْسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Return ye, and fight not; and bind it upon my head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning attach and attribute to me the disgrace that will befall you for relinquishing the battle and inclining to peace. (IAth, TA.) And it is said in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwmuwA bimaA EaSabakumo bihi","text_ar":"قُومُوا بِمَا عَصَبَكُمْ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fulfil ye the obligations with which He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning God)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has bound you;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which He has imposed upon you and attached to you;"},{"kind":"text","text":"by his commands and prohibitions. (TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbN","text_ar":"عِصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He grasped the thing with his hand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) A poet, cited by IAar, says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wakun~aA yaA qurayo$u A_i*aA EaSabonaA\n                      \n                     \n                        yajiYo'u EiSaAbunaA bidamK EabiyTi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we were, O Kureysh, when we grasped"},{"kind":"text","text":"our opponents,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such that our grasping brought fresh blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbunaA","text_ar":"عِصَابُنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"our grasping"},{"kind":"text","text":"those whom we opposed with the swords. (TA.) ―         -b10-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clung,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kept, to"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing. (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba AlmaA='a","text_ar":"عَصَبَ المَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by, the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotahu","text_ar":"بَيْتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man remained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stayed, in his house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent, not quitting it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b11-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went round, encompassed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing. (K.) It is said in a trad., of the angel Gabriel, on the day of Bedr,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado EaSaba raA^osahu AlgubaAru","text_ar":"قَدْ عَصَبَ رَاْسَهُ الغُبَارُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The dust had overspread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and clung to, his head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado EaSama vaniy~atayohi","text_ar":"قَدْ عَصَمَ ثَنِيَّتَيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgubaAru","text_ar":"الغُبَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and if this be not a mistake, the latter verb is syn. with the former:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"being often interchangeable: (L, TA:) the latter phrase means, as also with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the dust had stuck to his two central incisors."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESm","text_ar":"عصم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And Ibn Ahmar says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*o EaSaba Aln~aAsa $amaAlN waqurN"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waquro","text_ar":"وَقُرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqur~N","text_ar":"وَقُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When north wind and cold environ me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) And one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba AlgubaAru biAljabali","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الغُبَارُ بِالجَبَلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The dust encompassed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounded, the mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabuwA bihi","text_ar":"عَصَبُوا بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They encompassed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounded, him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, O, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they encompassed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounded, him, looking at him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) and, (Msb, K,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSibuwA","text_ar":"عَصِبُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor. of the former"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and aor. of the latter"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they assembled around him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for fight"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb. For another explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiba","text_ar":"عَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see 12.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Alqawomu biAln~asabi","text_ar":"عَصَبَ القَوْمُ بِالنَّسَبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaATuwA bihi","text_ar":"اَحَاطُوا بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, included,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprehended, the relations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinsmen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~asabu","text_ar":"النَّسَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is often used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awuw Aln~asabi","text_ar":"ذَوُو النَّسَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabati AlA_ibilu biAlmaA='i","text_ar":"عَصَبَتِ الاـِبِلُ بِالمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels surrounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"encircled, the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Alr~iyqu bifiyhi","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الرِّيقُ بِفِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, * TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiba","text_ar":"عَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The saliva became dry in his mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyqu faAhu","text_ar":"الرِّيقُ فَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The saliva"},{"kind":"text","text":"by its drying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made his mouth dry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the saliva adhered to his mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Aboo-Mohammad El-Fak'asee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaEoSibu faAhu Alr~iyqu A^aY~a EaSobi\n                      \n                     \n                        EaSoba AljubaAbi bi$afaAhi AlwaTobi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The saliva makes his mouth dry, with what a drying ! as the drying of the spume of camels' milk on the lips of the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba fuwhu","text_ar":"عَصَبَ فُوهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His mouth, with"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2058},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his saliva, became dry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Alfamu","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الفَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSuwbN","text_ar":"عُصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the latter accord. to the explanation in the K,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dirty, from dust and the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from vehement thirst,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSuwbN","text_ar":"عُصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hungry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very hungry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his bowels were almost dried up with hunger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is said of the practice of a hungry man's binding round his belly, as expl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoSuwbN","text_ar":"مَعْصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba AlA^ufuqu","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الاُفُقُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horizon became red."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O. [In Freytag's Lex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiba","text_ar":"عَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as from the K, in which I do not find it. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiba","text_ar":"عَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) with kesr, (S, O,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariHa","text_ar":"فَرِحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) said of flesh, or flesh-meat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It had many"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinews,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendons"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiba","text_ar":"عَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [so in the TA, and so in a verse there cited, not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabN","text_ar":"عَصَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, firm and compact in flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  [Other meanings of this verb have been mentioned above.]"}],"source_refs":["K","S","A","Mgh","O","TA","Msb","L"]},{"entry_id":"n29266","headword_ar":"عصّب","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, O, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoSiybN","text_ar":"تَعْصِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, O,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound round,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with several circumvolutions:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound round"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a man's head with a turban, fillet, bandage, or the like; (S, * O, * Msb, K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"a broken limb, or a wound, with a piece of rag or a bandage. (L, TA.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turbaned"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attired"},{"kind":"text","text":"him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a turban."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (A, O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoSiybN","text_ar":"تَعْصِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)  [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crowning"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man: (see the pass. part. n.:)] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a chief:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, O, K, TA:) for turbans are the crowns of the Arabs: (O:) when a man's people made him a chief, they bound his head with a turban: (A, TA:) as kings wore crowns, so the chiefs of the Arabs wore red turbans: (L, TA:) there were brought to the desert, from Haráh ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haraAp","text_ar":"هَرَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"), red turbans, which the nobles among the Arabs wore. (Az, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ES~bhu biAls~ayofi","text_ar":"عصّبهُ بِالسَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~amahu bihi","text_ar":"عَمَّمَهُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wounded, him in the place of the turban, with the sword"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ES~bhu","text_ar":"عصّبهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused him to bind his waist by reason of hunger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see the pass. part. n.:) and hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made him to hunger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaS~abatohumu Als~inuwna","text_ar":"عَصَّبَتْهُمُ السِّنُونَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The years of drought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sterility, made them to hunger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ES~bthu Als~inuwna","text_ar":"عصّبتهُ السِّنُونَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The years of drought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sterility, ate up his property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cattle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, S, O.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. drought or the like]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroyed him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ES~b Ald~ahoru maAlahu","text_ar":"عصّب الدَّهْرُ مَالَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Adverse fortune destroyed his cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He called him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaS~ab","text_ar":"مُعَصَّب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poor"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so says IAar; and he cites as an ex.,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yudoEaY AlmuEaS~aba mano qal~ato Haluwbatuhu\n                      \n                     \n                        wahalo yuEaS~abu maADiY Alham~i miqodaAmu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is called the poor, whose milch-cattle have become few: but should one whose purpose is effectual, one of great boldness, be called poor?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~akaru yuEaS~ibu AlA^unovaY","text_ar":"الذَّكَرُ يُعَصِّبُ الاُنْثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The male makes the female to be such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabapN","text_ar":"عَصَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by his being consociated with her as such]. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","O","MA","K","TA","L"]},{"entry_id":"n29271","headword_ar":"عَصْبٌ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbapN","text_ar":"عِصَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  And see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSobN","text_ar":"عُصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A particular sort of the garments called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fabric of El-Yemen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the yarn is dyed, and then woven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the yarn is put together and bound, then dyed, and then woven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, TA; *) not of the sort called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdu Alr~aqomi","text_ar":"بُرُودُ الرَّقْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) it has no pl., (Nh, Msb, TA,) nor dual: (Msb:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodu EaSobK","text_ar":"بُرْدُ عَصْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, Mgh, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdu EaSobK","text_ar":"بُرُودُ عَصْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, Mgh, Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yurodaA EaSobK","text_ar":"يُرْدَا عَصْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yurodN EaSobN","text_ar":"يُرْدٌ عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdN EaSobN","text_ar":"بُرُودٌ عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Nh, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arodiyapu AlEaSobi","text_ar":"اَرْدِيَةُ العَصْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, TA;) and sometimes they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"being known by this name: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fabric of El-Yemen, the yarn of which is put together and bound, and then dyed, and woven, so that they become partycoloured, because what has been bound thereof remains white, the dye not having taken it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and such garments a woman in the period termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eid~ap","text_ar":"عِدَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] is allowed to wear, but not garments that are [wholly] dyed: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"striped garments of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"text","text":": and what is forbidden in that case is a garment that has been dyed after it has been woven; or what are forbidden are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSob","text_ar":"عَصْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of El-Yemen, which are said to have been dyed with urine; so in the L &c.: (TA:) or, accord. to Sub,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fabric of El-Yemen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because they are dyed with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSob","text_ar":"عَصْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", which grows only in El-Yemen; [he says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaSobu","text_ar":"العَصْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain dyed that does not grow but in El-Yemen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)] but in this he opposes the generality of authorities; for they agree in stating that the garments in question are thus called from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaSobu","text_ar":"العَصْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ the act of binding, ” because the yarn is bound in order that the dye may not pervade the whole of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MF, TA.) ―         -b4-  Hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clouds like such as are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laTox","text_ar":"لَطْخ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red clouds"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mist"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seen in the western horizon"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a time of drought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sterility;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbapN","text_ar":"عِصَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAy^ibu","text_ar":"عَصَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  In a trad., mention occurs of a necklace made of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSob","text_ar":"عَصْب"},{"kind":"text","text":": ElKhattábee says, if it do not mean the garments of El-Yemen, I know not what it is; yet I see not how a necklace can be made of these: Aboo-Moosà thinks it may be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSab","text_ar":"عَصَب"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning the tendons of joints, as they may have taken the tendons of certain clean animals, and cut them in pieces, and made them like beads, and, when dry, made neck laces of them; but he adds his having been told by some of the people of El-Yemen that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain beast of the sea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the great river,"},{"kind":"text","text":"called also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasu firoEawona","text_ar":"فَرَسُ فِرْعَوْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pharaoh's horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"perhaps meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hippopotamus"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the teeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bones of which"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beads and other things, as the handles of knives &c., are made, and which is white."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2059},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Saliva that sticks and dries in the mouth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lafaZa fulaAnN EaSobahu","text_ar":"لَفَظَ فُلَانٌ عَصْبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one died."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lfZ","text_ar":"لفظ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A4-  And A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an active, and sharp-headed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"boy, or young man; (IAar, TA;) [and] so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDobN","text_ar":"عَضْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EDb","text_ar":"عضب"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","O","K","TA","Nh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n29272","headword_ar":"عُصْبٌ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabN","text_ar":"عَصَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain trees that twine round other trees, having weak leaves;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of tree called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labolaAb","text_ar":"لَبْلَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dolichos lablab"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.]; (K;) said by Sh to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of plant that twines round trees, i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labolaAbN","text_ar":"لَبْلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [coll. gen. ns.:] the ns. un. are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSobapN","text_ar":"عُصْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobapN","text_ar":"عَصْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabapN","text_ar":"عَصَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) accord. to Abu-lJarráh, (O, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobapN","text_ar":"عَصْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that twines about a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanaAdap","text_ar":"قَنَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tragacanth"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (O, K, TA,) thus, correctly, in many copies of the K, but in some"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataAp","text_ar":"فَتَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in some"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanaAp","text_ar":"قَنَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":", both of which are wrong, though some assert the latter to be correct, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not to be pulled off from it but with an effort:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA:) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiTofapN","text_ar":"عِطْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] one says of a man strong in struggling for the mastery,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qataAdapN luwiyato biEuSobapK","text_ar":"قَتَادَةٌ لُوِيَتْ بِعُصْبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tragacanth twined about by a lebláb;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the strong man being app. likened to a tragacanth, and his antagonist to a lebláb]: (TA:) and in a trad. of Ez-Zubeyr Ibn-El-'Owwám, he is related to have said,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Ealiqotuhumo A_in~iY xuliqotu EuSobaho\n                      \n                     \n                        qataAdapF taEal~aqato binu$obaho"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) he puts"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESbh","text_ar":"عصبه"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elqh","text_ar":"علقه"},{"kind":"text","text":", [evidently, I think, a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaliqFA","text_ar":"عَلِقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu$obapN","text_ar":"نُشْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in its proper art., for a confirmation,)] the meaning being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlqt Elqp lxSwmY","text_ar":"خلقت علقة لخصومى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in which for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elqp","text_ar":"علقة"},{"kind":"text","text":"I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaliqFA","text_ar":"عَلِقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; then he likens himself to a tragacanth in respect of his excessive tenaciousness; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bn$bh","text_ar":"بنشبه"},{"kind":"text","text":"means “ by the help of a thing of great tenaciousness: ” [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n$bh","text_ar":"نشبه"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be here an inf. n., i. e. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na$iba","text_ar":"نَشِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the meaning of the verse may therefore be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I clung to them: verily I have been created a grasper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tragacanth that has clung by means of a strong holdfast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has clung with great tenaciousness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA:) Sh explains"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSobap","text_ar":"عُصْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA) with damm on the authority of Ed-Deenawaree [i. e. AHn], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobap","text_ar":"عَصْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"with fet-h on the authority of AA, (O,) as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant that twines about a tree, and is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labolaAb","text_ar":"لَبْلَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu$obap","text_ar":"نُشْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning a man who, when he sports with a thing ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabiva bi$aYo'K","text_ar":"عَبِثَ بِشَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but probably the right reading is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abiva b$Y'","text_ar":"شَبِثَ بشىء"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$ab~ava","text_ar":"تَشَبَّثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. clings to a thing]), hardly, or never, quits it. (O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","O"]},{"entry_id":"n29273","headword_ar":"عَصَبٌ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinews,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendons;"},{"kind":"text","text":"though the following explanation seems rather to denote the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ligaments;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAb","text_ar":"اَطْنَاب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the joints,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which connect and bind together the structure thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in man and in others, such as the ox-kind, and sheep or goats, and gazelles, and ostriches; so says AHn; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabN","text_ar":"عَقَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S and K &c. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqb","text_ar":"عقب"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are yellow of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ATnAb","text_ar":"اطناب"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the joints;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqab","text_ar":"عَقَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the white: (Mgh:) [it is also used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ligaments:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see an ex. of its n. un. in an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~adafataAni","text_ar":"الصَّدَفَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadafN","text_ar":"صَدَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and sometimes it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nerves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see a usage of its pl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaroEN","text_ar":"صَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it is a coll. gen. n.:] the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, TA:) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoSaAbN","text_ar":"اَعْصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mgh, O, Msb.) ―         -b2-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in a pl. sense)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a people"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSobN","text_ar":"عُصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n29274","headword_ar":"عَصِبٌ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"Flesh, or flesh-meat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having many"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSab","text_ar":"عَصَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinews,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendons"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}